[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test coverage**\n\nI'm considering if we should include a negative path test while focusing on an uncovered call site. It seems like using `assertThatThrownBy(() -> JSON.std.beanFrom(Class.class, \"\\\"no.such.Type\\\"\"))` could be useful to trigger `Class.forName` and hit the exception path. While coverage appears focused on the call site, I think having a negative test with a dynamic name would help ensure the call occurs, especially if it fails due to an invalid name. Combining it with a positive path test could also strengthen the coverage.\n\n**Improving test coverage**\n\nI'm considering implementing two tests for better coverage. The first one could be `resolvesTopLevelNestedClassFromStringValues`, potentially utilizing `SimpleValueReaderDynamicAccessTestSupport.class.getName()` for the nested static final class. The second test would aim to surface missing classes as `JSONObjectException` using a helper for the missing class name. While I think we might not need additional property or collection tests, it’s worth keeping existing property/map/list tests to maintain coverage related to `TypeHolder`. Refining existing tests for targeted coverage seems like the way to go!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ee5382eb719f5cb0169f02febc2a4819d985141530547e4b0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8C_-pLr4uW5snTWv1R_hCV96ekY10m-jtV-6fv_BWfEeB2hdmI8TDkMEJDTx7zFG0h_U5UGL2yKE603DDB6cz6HC2jeRmcQvKJt_DynpljHGvKJ6E5J_ojIWAQR-naAMKxjkEOrM0lgR8uvTCINF3q9xjTlj-9xnJyTaqQT_tu7ipZZHG1e5UPyLFiQpw_MQUmYu-1sjkHmLQeoR9WY9sfhopCMPbEB6BCQlxjeNiO6P8jntEhqXUwmPXlZsEOylPl7Cz4ufKQeJAYotgn258qePoJvvwnNS9M-0K7v3p7ShfYfEUGsjDdr2HeDO7l7ohhEjOZ6s7aAfYEzFXrnwGu6LBpQZrPvPymp19AK2SVlFE7T16l9EXA3cpoqby4AjUMNvx9d8ILvr7zx-TGk_xVrjDeXPEzeXPO_wpn3iv4MI5f-gy42kC5Rh4paUwidbIXBnfiUwWDP051YTsI8ginTfe0bnHUUXdig70LpDxAYGbKPQLVzoJDQfDlydttUbn0eAKvQJ1F8MalIKfzo1hjY18Y